com.kuka.roboticsAPI.sensorModel

Class RecorderConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.sensorModel.RecorderConfiguration

  • public final class RecorderConfiguration
extends Object
    Provides information about the configuration of the IDataRecorder.

    This configuration is built by a RecorderConfigurator and is immutable.

      • getTimeoutMillisecs

        public int getTimeoutMillisecs()
        Gets the timeout of the recording in [ms].

        This value is used if the recording was not stopped before, either manually or by a trigger. A negative value means that no timeout will be used and the recording process will be stopped when the file size reaches 16MB or 30000 data sets are gathered.

        Returns:
        The timeout in [ms].

      • getURL

        public URL getURL()
        Gets the URL of the file where recorded data will be saved.

        If the data recording is invoked twice with the same file name the recording process overwrites the last file.

        Returns:
        the URL of the file recorded data will be saved
